  "prompt": "Is it a symptom of OCD to repeat words? (Repetitive, words and speech)",
  "response": "Repetitive speech or word repetition can be associated with OCD (Obsessive-Compulsive Disorder), but it's not always a definitive symptom. Some ways this might manifest include:\n\n1. Compulsive repeating of words or phrases\n2. Mental checking or repeating words internally\n3. Saying things \"just right\" to feel comfortable\n4. Repeating words to prevent perceived negative outcomes\n\nHowever, repetitive speech can also be related to:\n- Anxiety disorders\n- Tourette syndrome\n- Autism spectrum disorders\n- Certain neurological conditions\n\nA professional diagnosis is important to understand the specific cause and context of repetitive speech. If this is causing significant distress, it's recommended to consult a mental health professional who can provide a comprehensive evaluation.",
